Using a feature branch style approach, I call my parent task branch:

{{PROJECT-1567/master}}

When i create a subtask with a branch, it would be useful to detect the parent branch and give me the option to name my child branch as:

{{PROJECT-1567/PROJECT-1568-my-sub-task}}

Inline display of images works when bitbucket parses a {{readme.md}} file in markdown format. However, support for explicitly setting the display size of an image is not present.

For example:

{code}
![Some alt text](/private/image.png =250x)
{code}

should include the file "/private/image.png", and set the width of the image to 250 pixels.

I can&#x27;t push my branches to the online-repo anymore. I always get an 500-error:

{code}
#!Command
$ git push
fatal: unable to access &#x27;https://xxxx@bitbucket.org/xxxx/xxxx.git/&#x27;: The requested URL returned error: 500

{code}
